<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="492" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="11.[783,1378,2619,3038]" pageId="11" pageNumber="492">
The widely separated subpopulations of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Milne-Edwards" box="[784,919,2817,2842]" class="Mammalia" family="Phalangeridae" genus="Phalanger" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diprotodontia" pageId="11" pageNumber="492" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="vestitus">P vestitus</taxonomicName>
are distinctive, and their taxonomy needs to be reevaluated; it is likely more than one species is involved. Three subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="492" type="distribution">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6657461" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6657461" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6657461/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="492" targetBox="[169,760,2622,3036]" targetPageId="11">
